results.definition: characterized by an absence or near absence of agitation or activity
examples: the factions remained quiet for almost 10 years

results.definition: free of noise or uproar; or making little if any sound
examples: a quiet audience at the concert
the room was dark and quiet

results.definition: (of a body of water) free from disturbance by heavy waves
examples: a ribbon of sand between the angry sea and the placid bay
the quiet waters of a lagoon
a lake of tranquil blue water reflecting a tranquil blue sky
scarcely a ripple on the still water

results.definition: of the sun characterized by a low level of surface phenomena like sunspots e.g.
